Let

 T(k)=1+3 k(k+1)  be the last number on the k-th “ring’’ of the hexagonal spiral  
  (ring 0 contains only the central 1, ring 1 the numbers 2 … 7, ring 2 the numbers 8 … 19, …).

1.  Which ring holds 2026?  
 Solve   T(k−1)<2026 ≤ T(k)

 T(25)=1+3·25·26=1951   < 2026  
 T(26)=1+3·26·27=2107   ≥ 2026  

 So 2026 lies on ring 26 (k=26).

2.  Index of 2026 on its ring  
 The first number on ring 26 is T(25)+1=1952.  
 Index (0-based) j = 2026−1952 = 74.

 With ring length 6k = 156, split j into  
  segment s = ⌊j/k⌋ = ⌊74/26⌋ = 2,  
  step  t = j mod k  = 74−52   = 22.

3.  The six neighbours  
 • two on the same ring: 2026−1 = 2025 and 2026+1 = 2027.  

 • two on the inner ring (k−1 = 25, length 150, first number 1802):  
  inner indices  = s(k−1)+t−1 ,  s(k−1)+t  
   = 2·25+21 = 71 , 2·25+22 = 72  

  inner numbers = 1802+71 = 1873, 1802+72 = 1874.

 • two on the outer ring (k+1 = 27, length 162, first number 2108):  
  outer indices  = s(k+1)+t ,  s(k+1)+t+1  
   = 2·27+22 = 76 , 77  

  outer numbers = 2108+76 = 2184, 2108+77 = 2185.

4.  Sum of the six neighbours  
 2025 + 2027 + 1873 + 1874 + 2184 + 2185  
 = (2025+2027) + (1873+1874) + (2184+2185)  
 = 4052 + 3747 + 4369  
 = 12 168.

Answer: 12168
